            </div>

           
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12762.xml">letter from T. H. Farrer, 16 October 1880</ref> and n. 5.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, p. 18, CD stated that it was probable that the little stones and similar material swallowed by worms were used like millstones to grind their food.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5039.xml">Elizabeth Wedgwood</ref> was seriously ill (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-12748.xml">letter from T. H. Farrer, 9 October 1880</ref> and n. 5); Farrer was married to her niece <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5028.xml">Katherine Euphemia (Effie) Farrer</ref>.</note>
